CIESIN, the Center for International Earth Science Information Network at Columbia University, authorizes the Australian government Agency for International Development (AusAID) to use the Data, listed below, to develop and distribute the InaSAFE (Indonesia Scenario Assessment for Emergencies) open source tool for rapid assessment of impact to buildings, infrastructure and population from natural disasters.

Center for International Earth Science Information Network (CIESIN), Columbia University; and Centro Internacional de Agricultura Tropical (CIAT). 2005. Gridded Population of the World Version 3 (GPWv3): Population Density Grid. Palisades, NY: Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center (SEDAC), CIESIN, Columbia University. Available at http://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/gpw.

Except as noted above, CIESIN does not assign AusAID any rights to authorize third-party redistribution of the Data. In accepting the Data, AusAID agrees to acknowledge the individual authors and CIESIN at Columbia University as the source of the Data, to display the URL (http://www.ciesin.columbia.edu) for the CIESIN website within the acknowledgement statement, and to provide CIESIN with a copy of any publication that includes the Data. AusAID also agrees to release CIESIN and Columbia University from any liability resulting from any use of the Data by AusAID or by any other parties.

Please feel free to contact us if you have any questions.

